PAUL PATON of Dundee United and former Stenhousemuir player Chris McCluskey have been arrested over an alleged assault on the Hoops player in Ashton Lane last week. Two footballers arrested over attack on Celtic goalkeeper Lukasz Zaluska in Glasgow street - Daily Record FOOTBALLERS Paul Paton and Chris McCluskey have been arrested in connection with an alleged assault on Celtic player Lukasz Zaluska.
The arrests follow an incident involving the 32-year-old goalkeeper in Glasgow's Ashton Lane in the early hours of October 20.
A Police Scotland spokeswoman said: &quot;Two men aged 26 and 27 have been arrested in relation to the incident. They have since been released.
&quot;A full report will be submitted to the procurator fiscal.&quot;
Paton, 27, plays as a midfielder for Dundee United. Goalkeeper McCluskey, 26, is currently without a club. He most recently played for Stenhousemuir.
The men are expected to appear at Glasgow Sheriff Court on November 27.
 